<TITLE> 5 killed in road mishaps in 3 districts </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 1 (bdnews24.com)  Five persons were killed in four road accidents across the country. In Chittagong, two persons were killed and three others injured in a road accident at Patia upazila on Saturday. The accident occurred at around 11:30am when a bus and an auto rickshaw collided in front of Saleh Nur College of the upazila, said Patia police chief Imtiaz Ahmed. The dead were identified as Lucky Akhtar, 27, and Abdul Jabbar, 26, the auto rickshaw driver. The injured are Lucky's mother Kulsuma Akhter, 50, and her two sons Hasan Ali, 4 and Hannan Ali, 2. They were taken to Chittagong Medical College Hospital. Imtiaz said that Lucky died on the spot and the other died on the way to CMCH. The auto rickshaw was wrecked and the driver of the bus fled, the police official added. bdnews24.com Gazipur correspondent reported that a garment worker was killed when a bus ran him over bus near Bagherbazar. The victim, Shafiqul Islam, 25, was a worker of EP Tex, an apparel factory in the area. After his death the public barricaded the road. They also vandalised at least five cars, the police added. Due to this, traffic movement came to a halt on Dhaka-Mymensingh highway for nearly an hour. Traffic movement resumed at around noon after the situation was brought under control, said sub inspector of highway police in Naojor sub station Mostafizur Rahman. Mostafiz told bdnews24.com that Shafiq's bi-cycle was hit by a bus of Prabhati Banasri Paribahan at around 11am at Bagherbazaar area. He died on the spot. After the accident, the locals came on to the road and stopped traffic. They demanded construction of a speed breaker at Bagherbazar. The road block was removed after the police assured them of taking necessary actions, the official added. In another accident Nurul Islam, 55, was killed when run over by a bus of Ajmeri Paribahan. According to the police, the accident took place at around 11:30am in Bara Bari area of the Dhaka-Mymensingh highway. The police said that he was hit while crossing the road and died on the spot. bdnews24.com from Bagerhat reported that an old woman was killed in a road accident in the town on Saturday. The dead, Moyna Begum, 80, wife of Ismail Hossain, is from the East Basahati area. Md Shahjahan, sub inspector of Bagerhat Sadr Police Station, told bdnews24.com that a truck, carrying sand, had run over the elderly woman at KB Bazaar area of Bagerhat town protection dam at around 10am. She died on the spot. The body was sent to Bagerhat Sadr Hospital for post mortem, the official said. Police seized the truck. bdnews24.com
